DESeq2

Test perforamces DESeq2 with the pseudobulk counts obtained previously.

library(DESeq2)
library(tidyverse)
library(pheatmap)
library(RColorBrewer)

Load counts and experiment design

counts <- read.csv("Pseudobulk_clean_healthy.csv", row.names = "Symbol")
exp_design <- read.csv("Experiment_design_healthy.csv", row.names = "Sample")
cts <- as.matrix(counts)

exp_design$Condition <- factor(exp_design$Condition)
exp_design$Batch <- factor(exp_design$Batch)

head(exp_design)
##                               Condition       Batch
## NK_exhausted_Healthy_BM_1  NK_exhausted PRJNA492227
## NK_exhausted_Healthy_BM_10 NK_exhausted PRJNA492227
## NK_exhausted_Healthy_BM_11 NK_exhausted PRJNA492227
## NK_exhausted_Healthy_BM_12 NK_exhausted PRJNA492227
## NK_exhausted_Healthy_BM_13 NK_exhausted PRJNA492227
## NK_exhausted_Healthy_BM_14 NK_exhausted PRJNA492227
all(rownames(exp_design) %in% colnames(cts))
## [1] TRUE
all(rownames(exp_design) == colnames(cts))
## [1] TRUE
dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = cts,
                              colData = exp_design,
                              design = ~ Batch + Condition)
dds
## class: DESeqDataSet 
## dim: 8390 66 
## metadata(1): version
## assays(1): counts
## rownames(8390): A1BG A2M-AS1 ... ZYX ZZEF1
## rowData names(0):
## colnames(66): NK_exhausted_Healthy_BM_1 NK_exhausted_Healthy_BM_10 ...
##   NK_resident_Healthy_CD138n_8 NK_resident_Healthy_CD138n_9
## colData names(2): Condition Batch
vsdata <- vst(dds, nsub = 600, blind=FALSE)
plotPCA(vsdata, intgroup = "Condition")

vsdata_mat <- assay(vsdata)
vsdata_corr <- cor(vsdata_mat)
# Plot heatmap
pheatmap(vsdata_corr, annotation = exp_design[, c("Condition"), drop=F])

dds$Condition <- factor(dds$Condition, levels = c("NK_resident","NK_exhausted"))
dds <- DESeq(dds, test="LRT", full = ~ Batch + Condition, reduced = ~ Condition)
res = results(dds)# contrast=c("Condition", "Aberrant erythroid", "Pro B cells"))

sig_res <- subset(res, padj < 0.05 & abs(log2FoldChange) >= 0.3)
res_tbl <- res %>%
        data.frame() %>%
        rownames_to_column(var="gene") %>%
        as_tibble()

sig_res_tbl <- sig_res %>%
        data.frame() %>%
        rownames_to_column(var="gene") %>%
        as_tibble()



dim(res_tbl)
## [1] 8390    7
dim(sig_res_tbl)
## [1] 147   7
plotDispEsts(dds)

## Obtain logical vector where TRUE values denote padj values < 0.05 and fold change > 1.5 in either direction
res_table_thres <- res_tbl %>% 
                  mutate(threshold = padj < 0.05 & abs(log2FoldChange) >= 0.3)
                  
## Volcano plot
ggplot(res_table_thres) +
    geom_point(aes(x = log2FoldChange, y = -log10(padj), colour = threshold)) +
    ggtitle("Volcano plot of stimulated B cells relative to control") +
    xlab("log2 fold change") + 
    ylab("-log10 adjusted p-value") +
    scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,50)) +
    theme(legend.position = "none",
          plot.title = element_text(size = rel(1.5), hjust = 0.5),
          axis.title = element_text(size = rel(1.25))) 

write_csv(sig_res_tbl, "DESeq2_healthy.csv")
